{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 14}For the {\scaps Lord} will take pity on Jacob, he will elect Israel once more and settle them on their own land: resident foreigners will join them and attach themselves to the household{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}of Jacob. (Foreign) people will take them and bring them to their place; and the household of Israel will employ them in the {\scaps Lord}\uc1\u8217*s land as men-servants and maid-servants, thus reducing their erstwhile captors to captivity, and lording it over those who had been their taskmasters.
